{
  "texts": [
    "There is currently insufficient empirical evidence to conclusively support the claim that AI-generated feedback consistently improves students' revisions of academic work, particularly in the context of academic writing in Hong Kong higher education.",
    "However, several studies provide valuable insights into the potential and challenges of using AI in educational settings.",
    "For example, research suggests that while students in Hong Kong find AI tools convenient for learning writing skills, teachers express concerns regarding the generality and ambiguity of AI feedback, indicating the need for more precise and context-specific feedback mechanisms (Cheng, 2024).",
    "Studies on hybrid intelligence, which integrates AI and human input, reveal that formative feedback targeting individual errors can enhance students' writing skills, as",
    "demonstrated in a study involving law students (Weber et al., 2024)."
  ]
}